text: Prayut Chan-o-cha (; born 21 March 1954) used to be a Thai army officer and was the Prime Minister of Thailand from 2014 to 2023. He was Commander-in- Chief of the Royal Thai Army. On 24 August, the Constitutional Court of Thailand suspended Prayut as prime minister, however Prayut still claims to be prime minister. As the most senior deputy prime minister, Prawit Wongsuwan was made acting prime minister. He became prime minister again from September 2022 to August 2023. ==Notes== ==References== Category:1954 births Category:Living people Prayut Chan-o-cha Prayut Chan-o-cha
